Well, Katie and I broke up about a 1 month 10 days ago.  I am still very hurt, but I hurt becuase I know I hurt Katie.  I still chat with her sometimes about life, and we had to communicate for her to move out of the apartment.  I am glad that we can still chat...and not fight.  I would love to meet her again in my lifetime, hopefull sooner then later.  I know I did ALOT wrong, and I didnt do ALOT right, but I will fight till my death to treat her like the princess she is.  I miss everything about her...I only wish she knew it.

So as usualy my mother has to ruin everything.  I was so excited to have an adult Thanksgiving, meaning, I was behaving, as well as my mother.  Things started out just fine until she did her usual I have to make everyone as unhappy as I am rutine.  I brought the wrong AV cable, so my mom cannot hook up her TV right, big fucking deal, she has to go one more day without TV.  But nooo....she has to make a big fucking deal out of it.  She started saying how she has no handy man around to do her things, and I was like ***roll my eyes*** (she just got divorced)  now she is going to play that card!!! So I went out of my way and went to Walgreens and some other stores, none of which were open or had the proper cord.  I come back to her condo eithout the cord, and all hell breaks loose.  She bitches about how nothing can get accomplished if she counts on me, and all that jazz.  I said "I dont have to be treated like this, I am leaving" and my grandparents were so upset because I was leaving, but I am sorry I dont have to be disrespected on a day I am supposed to enjoy.  So my mom tried to keep me there by saying dont leave, but I was going to leave no matter what. I walked to the elevator, and my grandmother begged me to stay, but I said I am sorry, I must leave, I will visit soon, and I left.  My heart was so sore from arguing with my mother, I just wanted a fun Thanksgiving minus the drama.  I guess I cannot escape the DRAMATIC life of my mother.  Oh to make things worse, my sister was going to be a bit late to my moms house, so I left before she even got there, and now my sister as mad at me for my mothers enragement.  Please, is TV important enough to destroy a family?  The love for my mother only hangs on by a thread, it is wearing very thin.

***walks away still teary eyed***

Well everyone.  It has been quite some time since I have written in my journal, let me just start by saying...I have been a raving bitch lately, not just to Katie, but to everyone.   I needed some alone time and I needed to just sit and think about things, not to mention the conversation I had with B.J. I got out a lot of stuff out that needed to be disgussed.  

Not too much has happened lately.  Same old same old, just working, sleeping, and trying to keep my self entertained so I do not get bored and go insane.  I don't really know if anyone is even interested in hearing this...but who cares, its my journal...so here goes.

I love fall, I love the way it looks, smells and just the thought of fall makes me so excited.  Its the time for Halloween (my all time favorie holidy) its the time for Thanksgiving...its so beautiful.  But with fall comes this odd feeling inside...my therapist a few years ago told me it was because everything around me was dying and I couldn't handle that...I don't agree...death doesn't bother me...despite the fact that I am alergic to fall and almost die...I love it.  I came to the conclusion a while ago that the smell and feel of fall makes me fall into this depression, It's a long and boring story, so if you don't want to read I suggest you stop now before you get sucked into my mental vortex.  

Fall to me is going back to school, its playing in leaves, its wearing a light sweater after a hot summer...my childhood ideals on fall...now fall is just like every other season...with memories.  I am not saying that I had this horrable childhood, but in junior high I didn't have very many friends and when school would start I would associate fall with having...screw it...

Anyway, my Katie is sick, and I hope she feels better soon.  I really want to do something special with her, but not when she is sick, she wouldnt enjoy it....

my shoes smell!

Amanda
